creator: Marie Corelli
description:
LibriVox recording of The Secret Power by Marie Corelli.
Read in English by Leena Emsley; Chris Hymans; Doodles; Vaughan McCarthy; Kathleen Moore; Trish E. Matson; ToddHW; Kristin Gjerløw; Harley James
This Marie Corelli novel falls in the realm of fantasy and science fiction with a steampunk element. The story centers around Morgana Royal, a powerful woman who invents an airship, and Roger Seaton, her love interest who has control of a destructive power. She explores her capacity to love, as well as his. Moreover, she questions whether she is of this world and this time, or some other realm altogether. - Summary by Amy Gramour
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
